-- MOVES-Lombard Odier Investment Managers hires former BlackRock exec
-- 
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 08:05AM EDT
-- None



Aug 11 (Reuters) - Lombard Odier Investment Managers named Nancy Everett, a former BlackRock Inc <BLK.N> executive, to the newly created post of senior advisor in its U.S. operations.

Everett will focus on traditional and alternative investment strategies at Lombard Odier Investment Managers (LOIM), the institutional asset management arm of Lombard Odier Group. Everett, who stepped down from BlackRock in December, was most recently managing director, head of U.S. Fiduciary Management at the world's largest money manager.